<DL compact>
  <DT>(a)=20
  <DD>The maximum currency amount that can be represented is <EM=20
  class=3Dvar>$x.99</EM> and the minimum is <EM class=3Dvar>-$x.99</EM>, =
where <EM=20
  class=3Dvar>x</EM> is <EM class=3Dvar>2<SUP>32</SUP>-1</EM>. However, =
if we plan=20
  to do any arithmetic on the currency amounts, then the limits are =
changed=20
  because our codes combine the dollar and cents amounts into a single =
<CODE=20
  class=3Dcode>long</CODE> by multiplying the dollar amount by 100 and =
then adding=20
  in the number of cents. When arithmetic is to be performed, the =
absolute value=20
  of the currency amount <EM class=3Dvar>$x.yy</EM> should be such that =
<EM=20
  class=3Dvar>100x + y &lt;=3D 2<SUP>32</SUP>-1</EM>.=20
  <DT>(b)=20
  <DD>When the data type of <CODE class=3Dcode>dollars</CODE> is changed =
to <CODE=20
  class=3Dcode>int</CODE>, the maximum currency amount that can be =
represented is=20
  $32,768.99 and the minimum amount is -$32,768.99 (note that one of the =
16 bits=20
  is reserved for a sign even though we never store a negative number).=20
  <DT>(c)=20
  <DD>See answer to (a). </DD></DL></FONT></BODY></HTML>

